4. Punica fide] “With Carthaginian bad faitb,'' a pro· verbial expression applied to the Moors and N umidians as well as to the actual Carthaginians. Comp. Lucan, iv. 736. ‘Ut Libycas metuat fraudes infectaque semper Punica bella dolis. For the proverbial bad saith attributed by the Romans to the Carthaginians‚ see Livy, xxi. 4 ; xxv. 393 xlii. 475 Flor. ii. 2. 63 Val. Max. vii. 4. 4, etc. Plautus has the phrase, Poenis Poenior.
